In a most recent study, the time interval between onset of symptoms in a population of 8,866 cases as described above was determined to be 4.8 (3.0-7.2) days.
The most important task for health officials is to shift the effective period of isolation based on the time intervals when symptoms appear, and by doing so, avoid infected but asymptomatic people spreading the virus to others.
