The major and early symptom of COVID-19 is fever, which may be accompanied by symptoms such as dry cough, shortness of breath, sore throat, fainting, headache, sore throat, runny nose, chest pain, stomach pain, nausea, and vomiting.
Some patients experienced shortness of breath and/or blood clots within a week of infection.
In severe cases, patients developed symptoms of hypertrophic shock, shock of the lungs, metabolic acidification and blood clot mutation.
Patients with symptoms of fever and/or respiratory distress and severe fever, even if no pulmonary disorders are present, should be screened during the initial diagnostic examination.
