In case of self-isolation, consumers are known to stockpile due to fear of COVID-19.
On Wednesday, Woolworths limited toilet paper purchases for home delivery to one package per serving.
The changes follow the previous four-packets-per-transaction restriction introduced by Woolworths and Coles on March 4 and 5, respectively.
In its March 8 press release, Coles called the demand "unprecedented" as four packet controls are in place, and "many stores are still selling out within an hour of distribution", while ALDI, in a Facebook post on Tuesday, called it "unexpected".
